Finally some exciting news for aquarium fans. Cape Town’s biggest underwater world has officially opened its doors to the public. The Two Oceans Aquarium was closed for more than five months because of the lockdown and for the longest time in its 25-year history. eNCA's Nobesuthu Hejana has the story.  CAPE TOWN - Finally some exciting news for aquarium fans. Cape Town’s biggest underwater world has officially opened its doors to the public. The Two Oceans Aquarium was closed for more than five months because of the lockdown and for the longest time in its 25-year history. The aquarium is a world-class tourist attraction that's all about conservation and education. Members of the public have been encouraged to book their tickets online to prevent overcrowding at the entrances. Although activities at the centre have been changed, management says visitors can expect fun new things to do soon.